fields.description:
This popup will appear when the user clicking on the "Add patient" button.
On the top of the popup, the header will show.
Under the header, a text of 3 rows will be shown (all of the text will be "hard-coded").
Besides the Name of the dietician.
Under the text, a checkbox with a text.
And then three fields:

# Name of parent \- will be nececry only if the age of the patient is under 18
# Signature \- use outsource SDK \- the user will need to sketch with his mouse, after sketching, the user can click on "Clear" to delete his sketch.

The user can click on "Cancel" button and close the page.
The user can click on "Approve" button and continue to "User details" popup.
Only after he:
1. marked the checkbox.
2. filled the signature field.
3. filled his parent name (if needed).

The user can click on "Fill later" and then move to "User half details" popup.
Moving to the "User half details" popup will save all the data that was filled in the Terms of use page in case that the user will decide to go back.
fields.summary: Add patient popup - Terms of use

issuetype.description: A user story. Created by JIRA Software - do not edit or delete.
issuetype.name: Story

fields.description:
After the user clicked on the "Fill later" button in the Terms of use page he will get to this page.
The page will have a header, text and two fields:

# The first letter of the first name.
# The first letter of the second name.
# The year of birth
# The month of birth (Only for a patient that under 18 years old).

The user can click on "Back" button and go back to Terms of use page (With all data saved).
The user can click on "Approve" button and continue to the full system.

In this case (filling "half detailed" and not "full detailed") the name of the user will be only the first letters and his date of birth will be only the year and month.

When the user will click on "Print" button the "Full details" popup will open and the user will have to fill it for printing.
The user can also fill the full details in the "User area" in the full system.
fields.summary: User half details page

fields.description:
As a user I will be able to see the "my last session" header

1.	The header, including the share and the menu options, has already been developed
2.	The header will include a text "My Last Session" and the current date, or if the current date is today - the writing "Today", and the time of the session 
2.1.	by tapping on the "My last session" or the date a pop up "choose Date" will appear
2.2	the "choose a date" pop up will include a date wheel - dd mm yyyy
2.3.	the user will be able to choose a session date
2.4.	by tapping the "cancel" button, user will close the pop-up
2.5.	by tapping the "go to session", user will go to the session information of the date he chose 
2.5.1.	the "my last session" headline will be change to the date of the session (dd MONTH, yyyy) and the hour that the session was conducted on
2.5.2.	By tapping on the "close" button user will be able to go back to the "my last session page"  
2.5.3.	If the user had more than one session in the date he chose he will be able to slide between those sessions  
2.5.3.1.	The sessions will be sorted from the earlier on the same date to the latest
fields.summary: My last session page - Header

fields.customfield_10402:
filter foods by groups will be a popup
The header "סינון קבוצות" will be on the top of the popup
The sub header "בחירת קבוצות מזון אשר אימון רצויות בתפריט" will be under the header
Two tabs will switch the content of the table:
מאכלים נפוצים
מאכלים נוספים
the content will come from the DB
In the table, the headers will be the categories.
The content will be the groups.
Clicking on a group, will mark the group in red and will make this group disappear from the "add food" suction.
Clicking on a group that all ready in red, will cancel the red mark and bring the group to be enable again on the "add food" suction.
Clicking on a header (Category) will act the same as clicking on a group, but will effect all of his groups.
If a category are mark in red (and all of his groups) and the user are clicking  on a red group
Switching between the tabs wont delete the changes.
Clicking on the "X" or the "Cancel" button will open a popup "are you sure you want to close.."
Clicking on the "Save" button will save the changes and go back to the "Menu settings".
fields.summary: Menu ---> Add food by nutrients.

fields.description:
Camera location to be configurable (for each camera):

# Offset of the middle of the sensor from the origin point (in mm)
# Orientation of the sensor (3 angles in degrees, representing ZXZ extrinsic Euler rotation, the
rotation is around the center of the sensor)
Calibration target parameters
Each calibration target is a flat surface with a black-and-white texture of a chessboard. For example:

For each calibration target we want to be able to configure:

# Size of the chessboard cell (in mm)
# Number of black squares along horizontal and vertical axes
# Offset of the center of the target from the origin point (in mm)
# Orientation of the calibration target (3 angles in degrees, representing ZXZ extrinsic Euler
rotation, the rotation is around the center of the calibration target)

fields.description:
Requirement overview:
Application for rendering views of calibration targets as seen by several cameras with given
parameters located at given positions.
Input:
Text file (in any format that is convenient, but easily editable by humans) containing:

# Number of cameras on the scene
# For each camera: parameters and location (see below)
# Number of calibration targets on the scene
# For each calibration target: parameters and location (see below)
Desired output:
# Renders from each of the camera (the scene is assumed to be uniformly illuminated)
# A render of an overview of the scene from which the location and orientation of the cameras
and calibration targets will be clear.
# The renders should be saved in lossless format (BMP or PNG)
Important:
The application should only use open-source/freeware components.
Parameters specification
Camera parameters to be configurable (for each camera):
# Focal length (in mm)
# Pixel pitch (in µm)
# Camera resolution (in pixels)
# ROI parameters (Origin X, Origin Y, Width, Height in pixels)

fields.description:
התוכן שישלט ע"י האדמין יהיו השאלות והתשובות של עמודים:

עמוד 3 ("Excited")

עמוד 4 ("Activities")

עמוד 7 ("Take care of")

:בכל עמוד התוכן שישלט הוא

השאלה הראשית טקסט חופשי - מוגבל ל40 תוים

הטקסט שמתחת לשאלה בטקסט חופשי - מוגבל ל90 תוים

השמות של התשובות בטקסט חופשי - מוגבל ל25 תוים

התמונות של התשובות - קבצי PNG\JPEG

ניתן לערוך תשובה

ניתן למחק תשובה

ניתן להוסיף תשובה

קיימת מגבלה של 40 תשובות לשאלה

https://xd.adobe.com/view/8ed962b8-dc56-4cc8-7e1f-7f4e41810829-f8e8/

התוכן צריך להשתנות לפי הגיל שנבחר בעמוד הראשון:

חלוקת הגילאים היא:

1-3

4-6

7-11
